items.title: Pittsburgh Quality Sleep Index (PSQI)
items.content: The following questions relate to your usual sleep habits during the past month only. Your answers should indicate the most accurate reply for the majority of days and nights in the past month. Please answer all questions.

items.label: During the past month, when have you usually gone to bed at night?

items.label: During the past month, how long (in minutes) does it usually take you to fall asleep each night?
items.name: PSQI-fallasleeptime

items.label: During the past month, when have you usually gotten up in the morning?
items.name: PSQI-wakeuptime

items.label: During the past month, how many hours of actual sleep did you get each night? (This may be different than the number of hours you spend in bed)
items.name: PSQI-hrsofsleep

options.label: Three or more times a week

items.name: PSQI-3wakeupbathroom

items.name: PSQI-4cannotbreathesleep

options.label: Three or more times a week

items.name: PSQI-5coughorsnoresleep

options.label: Three or more times a week

items.label: ...feel too cold
items.name: PSQI-6feeltoocold

options.label: Three or more times a week

items.name: PSQI-7feeltoohot

items.name: PSQI-8hadbaddreams

items.name: PSQI-9havepain

items.name: PSQI-overallsleepquality

options.label: Three or more times a week

items.label: During the past month, how often have you taken medicine (prescribed or "over the counter") to help you sleep?
items.name: PSQI-sleepmeds

options.label: Three or more times a week

items.label: During the past month, how often have you had trouble staying awake while driving, eating meals, or engaging in social activity?
items.name: PSQI-trblstayingawake

items.label: During the past month, how much of a problem has it been for you to keep up enough enthusiasm to get things done?
